    "Additionally, most CNNs of previous CADs relied on spatial information to accomplish the detection and classification.",
    "However, merging spatial and spectral knowledge could boost the detection and classification procedures.",
    "Moreover, several present CADs perform only binary classification of WSI into cancerous versus non-cancerous.",
    "Nevertheless, determining the sub-class of CRC is important to deciding the treatment and observation plans.",
    "In addition, many existing CADs have typically utilized a training dataset consisting of tens to hundreds of WSIs that have been meticulously annotated by professional pathologists to identify disease regions 33."
